# Prisma Relation Queries

Work with related data in [[prisma/client]] â€” loading, creating, connecting, and filtering across relations defined in [[prisma/schema]].

## Loading Relations

### include â€” Load full related records

```typescript
// Load user with all their posts
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  include: { posts: true },
});
// user.posts is Post[]

// Nested include â€” user with posts and each post's comments
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  include: {
    posts: {
      include: { comments: true },
    },
  },
});

// Filter included relations
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  include: {
    posts: {
      where: { published: true },
      orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
      take: 5,
    },
  },
});
```

### select â€” Return specific fields from relations

```typescript
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  select: {
    name: true,
    email: true,
    posts: {
      select: { id: true, title: true },
      where: { published: true },
    },
  },
});
// Type: { name: string; email: string; posts: { id: number; title: string }[] }
```

**Important:** `select` and `include` cannot be used together at the same level. Use `select` with nested `select` for full control.

### _count â€” Count related records

```typescript
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  include: {
    _count: { select: { posts: true, comments: true } },
  },
});
// user._count.posts, user._count.comments
```

## Nested Writes

### create â€” Create related records inline

```typescript
// Create user with posts in one query
const user = await prisma.user.create({
  data: {
    email: 'alice@example.com',
    name: 'Alice',
    posts: {
      create: [
        { title: 'First Post', content: 'Hello world' },
        { title: 'Second Post', content: 'More content' },
      ],
    },
    profile: {
      create: { bio: 'Developer' },
    },
  },
  include: { posts: true, profile: true },
});
```

### connect â€” Link to existing records

```typescript
// Create a post connected to an existing user
const post = await prisma.post.create({
  data: {
    title: 'New Post',
    author: { connect: { id: 1 } },
  },
});

// Connect multiple existing tags to a post
const post = await prisma.post.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: {
    tags: {
      connect: [{ id: 1 }, { id: 2 }, { id: 3 }],
    },
  },
});
```

### connectOrCreate â€” Connect if exists, create if not

```typescript
const post = await prisma.post.create({
  data: {
    title: 'Tagged Post',
    tags: {
      connectOrCreate: [
        {
          where: { name: 'typescript' },
          create: { name: 'typescript' },
        },
        {
          where: { name: 'prisma' },
          create: { name: 'prisma' },
        },
      ],
    },
  },
});
```

### set â€” Replace all connected records

```typescript
// Replace all tags on a post
const post = await prisma.post.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: {
    tags: { set: [{ id: 1 }, { id: 5 }] },
  },
});
```

### disconnect â€” Remove relation link

```typescript
// Disconnect a tag from a post (many-to-many)
const post = await prisma.post.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: {
    tags: { disconnect: [{ id: 3 }] },
  },
});

// Disconnect optional one-to-one
const user = await prisma.user.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: { profile: { disconnect: true } },
});
```

### Nested update and delete

```typescript
const user = await prisma.user.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: {
    posts: {
      update: {
        where: { id: 5 },
        data: { published: true },
      },
      deleteMany: { published: false },
    },
  },
});
```

## Relation Filters

Filter parent records based on properties of their related records.

### List relations: some, every, none

```typescript
// Users who have at least one published post
await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: {
    posts: { some: { published: true } },
  },
});

// Users where ALL posts are published
await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: {
    posts: { every: { published: true } },
  },
});

// Users with NO published posts
await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: {
    posts: { none: { published: true } },
  },
});
```

### Single relations: is, isNot

```typescript
// Posts where the author is an admin
await prisma.post.findMany({
  where: {
    author: { is: { role: 'ADMIN' } },
  },
});

// Posts where the author is NOT banned
await prisma.post.findMany({
  where: {
    author: { isNot: { status: 'BANNED' } },
  },
});
```

## Relation Patterns in Schema

See [[prisma/schema]] for how to define relations. Summary:

| Pattern | Schema | Notes |
|---------|--------|-------|
| One-to-many | `Post[] / @relation(fields:, references:)` | FK on "many" side |
| One-to-one | `Profile? / @relation(fields:, references:) + @unique` | `@unique` on FK |
| Many-to-many (implicit) | `Tag[] / Post[]` | Prisma manages join table |
| Many-to-many (explicit) | Define join model with `@@id` | Full control over join table |
| Self-relation | Named `@relation("Name")` | For trees, hierarchies |
